headline: UAW: GM Plan Shows Trump Tariffs Are Working
summary: United Auto Workers President Shawn Fain says General Motors’ plan to invest in U.S. factories shows President Trump’s automotive tariffs are working.  GM on Tuesday said it was bringing production of two gas-powered vehicles, the Chevrolet Blazer and Equinox, to the U.S. as part of a $4 billion plan to boost its U.S. production capacity to 2 million vehicles annually.  GM currently produces about 1.6 million vehicles a year in the country, according to consultancy AutoForecast Solutions.

headline: GM to invest $4 billion to shift some production from Mexico to the US
summary: Shares of General Motors rose before the opening bell after announcing plans to invest $4 billion to shift some production from Mexico to U.S. manufacturing plants as the automaker navigates tariffs that could drive prices higher.  President Trump signed executive orders in April, relaxing some of his 25% tariffs on automobiles and auto parts, a significant reversal as the import taxes threatened to hurt domestic manufacturers.  Automakers and independent analyses say the tariffs could raise prices, reduce sales and make U.S. production less competitive worldwide.
